{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778525867,"nonce":"44QnicByzDgj7V7FusmNqqbpUuo=","message":"**Metric correction — RMSE-of-profile-ratio supersedes CV as operative variance metric.**\n\nComment #13 ('Anti-anticipation 6-cell matrix outcomes') and #14 ('Comprehensive writeup') stated 'CV 0.007' as the headline metric for the combo cell. This was a misuse of CV (SD/mean of peak velocity scalar) as a drop-in for pairwise profile-RMSE ratio.\n\n**Corrected headline for the combo cell:**\n- vel-RMSE-ratio = **0.036** (was reported as CV=0.007 — different quantity)\n- 3 cells beat the \u003c 0.50 RMSE-ratio threshold: motor_pre (0.461), smooth_high (0.037), combo (0.036)\n- Loss-shape variants (Var A, Var B) fail on RMSE ratio (0.882, 1.131) as well as CV — deprioritization stands\n\n**Hold-motor diagnostic (new):** Motor commands during hold = 17.7% of movement magnitude in the combo cell. Drift is motor-command-driven, not mechanical. Increasing nn_output_pre_go is the targeted lever for further suppression.\n\nSee `results/2bc95fd/notes/variance_analysis.md` for full RMSE-primary table (post-merge).","files":null}]}